cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DS 

The paper deals with logical frameworks for expressing properties of distributed systems involving transactions. This involves concepts from concurrency theory, programming languages, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
